From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: [PATCH] ath11k: reject CE sends to an srng not yet rebuilt after fw recovery

During firmware-crash recovery ath11k_core_reconfigure_on_crash() calls
ath11k_hal_srng_clear() (memsetting srng_list, so src_ring.tp_addr becomes
NULL) and then clears ATH11K_FLAG_CRASH_FLUSH before
ath11k_core_qmi_firmware_ready() rebuilds the copy-engine srng in
ath11k_ce_init_pipes(). For the whole firmware boot the CRASH_FLUSH gate in
ath11k_ce_send() is already open while the CE srng is still zeroed.

A hostapd beacon update (nl80211_set_beacon -> ath11k_wmi_bcn_tmpl ->
ath11k_wmi_cmd_send -> ath11k_htc_send -> ath11k_ce_send) racing into that
window passes the CRASH_FLUSH check and dereferences the NULL
srng->u.src_ring.tp_addr in ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin(), a "Fatal
exception in interrupt".

Reject the send while that pointer is NULL. Testing tp_addr directly (rather
than srng->initialized) also closes the rebuild ordering window:
ath11k_hal_srng_setup() sets ->initialized before ->tp_addr without a
barrier, so an ->initialized check could still race the CE ring rebuild.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/ce.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/ce.c
@@ -751,6 +751,19 @@ int ath11k_ce_send(struct ath11k_base *a
 
 	srng = &ab->hal.srng_list[pipe->src_ring->hal_ring_id];
 
+	/* During firmware-crash recovery ath11k_hal_srng_clear() memsets the
+	 * srng_list and ATH11K_FLAG_CRASH_FLUSH is cleared before the copy-engine
+	 * srng is rebuilt in ath11k_core_qmi_firmware_ready().  A send racing into
+	 * that window would dereference the NULL src_ring.tp_addr in
+	 * ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin().  Test that exact field: ath11k_hal_srng_setup()
+	 * sets ->initialized before ->tp_addr (unbarriered), so an ->initialized check
+	 * would still race the rebuild.  Bail until the ring pointer is valid.
+	 */
+	if (unlikely(!srng->u.src_ring.tp_addr)) {
+		spin_unlock_bh(&ab->ce.ce_lock);
+		return -ESHUTDOWN;
+	}
+
 	spin_lock_bh(&srng->lock);
 
 	ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin(ab, srng);
